						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying on the south side of the Saṅgamēśvaraśvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>1531 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It is dated in Śaka 1453, Khara, Vaiśākha, ba. 3[0], Monday, corresponding to May 16 (f.d.t. °66) 1531 A.D.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. It registers the grant of toll-income on articles namely <hi rend="italic">pōṁkalu</hi> (betel nuts), <hi rend="italic">miryālu</hi> (pepper) <hi rend="italic">bellamu</hi> (jaggery), <hi rend="italic">nuvulu</hi> (rice), cereals per one bag <hi rend="italic">(gōnesaṁchi)</hi> passing through the Chimia kanuma, Pulivendala kanuma and Gaṇḍi Kanuma by the <hi rend="italic">Pekkaṁḍru,</hi> the followers of Gaurēśvara, Gaṇēśvaradēva, to the temple of Saṅgamēśvara and Vīrabhadra at Animala.</p>						

						</summary>
